Aragorn the King, Gandalf the sage, Frodo the ordinary man. 

All aspects of Christ, who combines all three.

@1954Portogh2 @CapturingChrist We have faith that they were. 

All the accounts of Alexander's life were from much later than that. Would you doubt he crossed the Hellespont and fought at Issues? Or reached the Indus then died in Babylon? Would you doubt Alexander's existence? 

Then why Christ's?

@PalamismRspctr @AleMartnezR1 @iWomansplainer The Socratic axiom is not all I KNOW is that I know nothing. It's I BELIEVE that I know nothing. 

Paul discusses our lack of ability to see the ultimate truth of things in Corinthians. For now we see only through dark glass. 

What is your definition of faith?
